# Pure PyTorch Implementation Rules

- Do not add MMDet3D/MMCV runtime dependencies in reimplementation modules.
- Prefer explicit tensor shapes in docstrings or comments for non-trivial transforms.
- Keep module boundaries close to paper blocks when feasible.
- Favor readable math-faithful code over framework-specific abstractions.
- Keep naming consistent with study docs and tests, including task namespace (`<task>/<model>`).
